  "prompt": "How I recover my Facebook password?",
  "response": "To recover your Facebook password, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook Login Page:**\n   Visit the Facebook website or open the app.\n\n2. **Click on 'Forgot Password?':**\n   Below the password field, click on the \"Forgot Password?\" link.\n\n3. **Enter Your Information:**\n   Enter the email address or phone number associated with your account, then click \"Search.\"\n\n4. **Choose Your Recovery Option:**\n   Facebook will show you a list of options to receive a code to reset your password (such as via email or SMS). Choose the one that works best for you, then click \"Continue.\"\n\n5. **Check Your Email or SMS:**\n   Check your email or SMS for the code sent by Facebook. Enter that code on the website/app.\n\n6. **Create a New Password:**\n   After entering the code, you'll be prompted to create a new password. Make sure it\u2019s strong and unique.\n\n7. **Log In:**\n   Once you've reset your password, you can log in to your Facebook account using the new password.\n\n8. **Secure Your Account:**\n   After logging in, consider updating your security settings, enabling two-factor authentication, and reviewing any recent logins and activity.\n\nIf you face any issues during the process, you can visit the Facebook Help Center for further assistance.",
